Request Tracker 4.0

1. aptitude install mysql-server rt4-db-mysql
2. service mysql [status|start|stop|restart]
3. aptitude install rt4-apache2
4. aptitude install request-tracker4
* Configuration:
     - name: typhoon.ocf.berkeley.edu
     - manage RT_SiteConfig.pam: yes
     - SQL password: ....
5. Go to /etc/request-tracker4 and pick a configuration (ours uses perl)
6. copy the configuration to /etc/apache2/sites-available
7. Add the following lines to /etc/apache2/sites-available/default before the ennding VirtualHost tag.
> Include /etc/request-tracker4/apache2-modperl2.conf <br />
> RedirectMatch ^/$ /rt <br />
8. Restart Apache
